The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Friday, March 12, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 The IFA will write to the AIFF to abolish the transfer-fee that is charged by some of the states during the inter-state transfer of players. The decision was taken in a meeting of the IFA with officials of Super Division clubs on Thursday. It was also decided that the IFA will ask for a modification of the lien rule. Currently, if a club takes a player on lien, they can have his services for the whole season. The IFA has proposed that the lien-period has to be for a minimum of two months, and then the deal should be open to discussion between the two concerned clubs.				 																																																	 South 24 Parganas beat Burdwan 1-0 in a final round match of the Konark Sheet state league at the Bidhannagar Sports Municipal Complex on Thursday. Indraneel Mukherjee scored the winner.				 																																																	 Somdev Varman of India made the quarter finals of the ITF Futures meet at the Saturday Club on Thursday, beating Febi Widhiyanto of Indonesia 7-5, 6-4. The other Indian to make the last-eight was Vinod Sridhar, who beat Vijay Kannan 6-0, 7-6.				 																																																	OTHER QUARTER FINALISTS				 																																																	Yordan Kanev (Bul), Noriaku Sugiyama (Jpn), Rainer Eitzinger (Aut), Todor Enev (Bul), Markus Egger (Aut), Jordanne Doble (Fra).				 																																																	 No play was possible on Day II of CAB Championship leg, play-off match between East Bengal and Ballygunge United on Thursday. The match will be replayed on March 17-18.				 																																																	FOOTBALL: National League  Mohun Bagan vs Haywards Sporting (Salt Lake Stadium, 3 pm)				 																																																	FOOTBALL: State league  Chandernagar vs Hooghly (Bidhannagar Municipal State Complex, 2:30 pm)				 																																																	TENNIS: ITF 